as.link <-
  function(x) {
    dplyr::case_when(
      # If x is like GO:003453
      startsWith(x, "GO:") ~ paste0(
        "<a target='_blank'",
        "href='", "http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/", x, "'",
        ">", x, "</a>"
      ),
      # Otherwise try this
      TRUE ~ paste0(
        "<a target='_blank'",
        "href='", "http://www.informatics.jax.org/marker/summary?nomen=", x, "'",
        ">", x, "</a>"
      )
    )
  }
show_de_table <- function(.) {
  (.) %>%
    select(base = baseMean, l2fc = log2FoldChange, p = pvalue, padj) %>%
    ind2col("symbol") %>%
    mutate(symbol = as.link(symbol)) %>%
    DT::datatable(escape = FALSE) %>%
    DT::formatSignif(c("base", "l2fc", "p", "padj"), digits = 3)
}
show_go_table <- function(.) {
  (.) %>%
    dplyr::select("category", "overrep.p", "#DE", "#cat", "term", "GO") %>%
    DT::datatable(escape = FALSE) %>%
    DT::formatSignif("overrep.p", digits = 3)
}

  vroom::vroom_write(., out_file(f), delim = "\t")

The following function constructs a SingleCellExperiment, while checking consistency of sample names.

make_sce <- function(counts, coldata) {
  # Check that samples in counts = genes x samples
  # are ordered as in coldata = samples x metafields
  stopifnot(assertthat::are_equal(colnames(counts), rownames(coldata)))
  SingleCellExperiment::SingleCellExperiment(
    assays = list(counts = counts), colData = coldata
  )
}

Misc

If A and B are SingleCellExperiment-like, then cosine computes the cosine similarity of of samples of A against samples of B.

cosine <- function(A, B) {
  A <- A@assays@data$counts
  B <- B@assays@data$counts
  ii <- intersect(rownames(A), rownames(B))
  A <- t(as.matrix(A[ii, , drop = FALSE]))
  B <- t(as.matrix(B[ii, , drop = FALSE]))
  A <- A / sqrt(rowSums(A * A))
  B <- B / sqrt(rowSums(B * B))
  A %*% t(B)
}

sce_cb <-
  make_sce(
    counts = (
      path_to("*/CasteloBranco-2018/*/expr.csv.gz") %>%
        from_csv()
    ),
    coldata = (
      path_to("*/CasteloBranco-2018/*/meta.csv.gz") %>%
        from_csv()
    )
  ) %>%
  # Only keep those cells
  `[`(, (.)$celltype %in% c("VLMC1", "VLMC2", "VLMC3", "VLMC4")) %>%
  # Order by cell type
  `[`(, order((.)$celltype))

Diagnostics

Attach diagnostics by scater.

sce_cb %<>% (function(sce) {
  scater::addPerCellQC(
    x = sce,
    subsets = list(Mito = grep("mt-", rownames(sce)))
  ) %>%
    scater::logNormCounts() %>%
    scater::runPCA(name = "PCA", ncomponents = 20) %>%
    scater::runTSNE(perplexity = 10, dimred = "PCA") %>%
    scater::runUMAP()
})

DE genes

  as.factor() %>%

de_results.vlmc3 <-
  sce_cb %>%
  {
    (.) %>%
      DESeq2::DESeqDataSet(design = ~celltype) %>%
      DESeq2::estimateSizeFactors() %>%
      DESeq2::DESeq(quiet = TRUE, fitType = "local") %>%
      DESeq2::results()
  } %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  slice_min(pvalue, n = 777)

Log2 fold-change is relative to VLMC3. Hence, negative l2fc means up in VLMC3.

de_results.vlmc3 %>%
  show_de_table()

Heatmap

sce_cb %>%
  list(
    sce = .,
    top = de_results.vlmc3 %>%
      slice_min(pvalue, n = 44) %>%
      arrange(log2FoldChange)
  ) %>%
  with({
    print(paste("Min abs log2 fold-change:", round(min(abs(top$log2FoldChange)), 2)))

    sce[rownames(top), ]
  }) %>%
  {
    pheatmap::pheatmap(
      log1p((.)@assays@data$logcount) %>% {
        # (.) / rowSums(.)
      },
      show_colnames = FALSE,
      cluster_cols = TRUE,
      cluster_rows = FALSE,
      treeheight_row = 0,
      treeheight_col = 0,
      fontsize = 6,
      color = grDevices::colorRampPalette(c("white", "black"))(10),
      annotation_col = (
        (.)@colData %>%
          as.data.frame() %>%
          select(celltype, group = Group)
      ),
      annotation_row = (
        de_results.vlmc3 %>%
          select(l2fc = log2FoldChange)
      )
    )
  }
## [1] "Min abs log2 fold-change: 2.02"

Compute GO

# Number of genes for GO analysis
n <- 33
enriched_go_terms <-
  de_results.vlmc3 %>%
  {
    list(
      up_vlmc3 = (.) %>% filter(log2FoldChange < 0),
      up_other = (.) %>% filter(log2FoldChange > 0)
    )
  } %>%
  lapply(function(.) {
    (.) %>%
      arrange(pvalue) %>%
      rownames()
  }) %>%
  within({
    f <- (function(x) x[1:5] %>% paste(collapse = ", "))
    print(paste("Up in VLMC3:", f(up_vlmc3), "..."))
    print(paste("Up in other:", f(up_other), "..."))
    rm(f)
  }) %>%
  lapply(function(de_results) {
    de_results %>%
      data.frame(symbol = .) %>%
      slice_head(n = n) %>%
      # Get the Entrez IDs of our genes
      merge(
        org.Mm.eg.db::org.Mm.egSYMBOL2EG %>% as.data.frame(),
        by = "symbol"
      ) %>%
      pull(gene_id) %>%
      # Enrichment analysis
      limma::goana(species = "Mm") %>%
      # Limit selection
      filter(P.DE <= 0.05) %>%
      arrange(P.DE) %>%
      # Format for display
      ind2col("category") %>%
      mutate(category = as.link(category)) %>%
      rename(
        # new name = old name
        "overrep.p" = P.DE, "#DE" = DE, "#cat" = N, "GO" = Ont, "term" = Term
      )
  })
## [1] "Up in VLMC3: Ptgfr, Moxd1, Col12a1, Col22a1, S1pr1 ..."
## [1] "Up in other: Mamdc2, F11r, Vit, Myoc, Ebf2 ..."

Cell-wise comparison

Castelo-Branco, 2018 vs Betsholtz, 2018.

This comparison depends a lot on the subset of genes along which to compare.

list(
  a = sce_cb,
  b = sce_bth_mb,

  # Select genes for comparison
  g = de_results.group %>% slice_min(pvalue, n = 150) %>% rownames()
) %>%
  with({
    # Keep only the common genes
    g <- intersect(g, intersect(rownames(a), rownames(b)))
  
    pheatmap::pheatmap(
      cosine(a[g, ], b[g, ]) %>% as.data.frame(),
      show_colnames = FALSE,
      show_rownames = FALSE,
      cluster_cols = TRUE,
      cluster_rows = TRUE,
      treeheight_row = 0,
      treeheight_col = 0,
      fontsize = 6,
      color = grDevices::colorRampPalette(c("white", "black"))(10),
      annotation_row = (
        a@colData %>%
          as.data.frame() %>%
          select(a = celltype)
      ),
      annotation_col = (
        b@colData %>%
          as.data.frame() %>%
          select(b = celltype)
      )
    )
  })
